on and Worcestershire), or Kerswill (Devon). See also   Caswell  ."]}]},{"name":"George","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Via Old French and Latin, from Greek <i>Georgios</i> (a derivative of <i>geōrgos</i> ‘farmer’, from <i>gē</i> ‘earth’ + <i>ergein</i> ‘to work’). This was the name of several early saints, including the shadowy figure who is now the patron of England (as well as of Germany and Portugal). If the saint existed at all, he was perhaps martyred in Palestine in the persecutions of Christians instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  at the beginning of the 4th century. The popular legend in which the hero slays a dragon is a medieval Italian invention. He was for a long time a more important saint in the Orthodox Church than in the West, and the name was not much used in England during the Middle Ages, even after  St George  came to be regarded as the patron of England in the 14th century. Its use increased from the 1400s, and by  1500  it was regularly among the most popular male names. This popularity was reinforced when  George I  came to the throne in  1714 , bringing this name with him from Germany. It has been one of the most popular English boys' names ever since."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":10,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"George Cresswell of Cresswell was born in 1445, in Northumberland, England as the son of John de Cresswell. He had at least 2 sons. He died in 1509, in England, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1445–1509":"1445–1509","1486–1534":"1486–1534","–Male":"Surnud","1412–1476":"1412–1476","1534":"1534","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","England":"England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Cresswell, Northumberland, England":"Cresswell, Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1445–1509":"1445–1509","1486–1534":"1486–1534","–Male":"Kuollut","1412–1476":"1412–1476","1534":"1534","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","England":"England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Cresswell, Northumberland, England":"Cresswell, Northumberland, England"},"fr":{"1445–1509":"1445–1509","1486–1534":"1486–1534","–Male":"Décédé","1412–1476":"1412–1476","1534":"1534","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","England":"Angleterre","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Angleterre","Cresswell, Northumberland, England":"Cresswell, Northumberland, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"George Cresswell of Cresswell est né en 1445, à Northumberland, Angleterre, fils de John de Cresswell. Il a eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé en 1509, à Angleterre, à l’âge de 64 ans."},"de":{"1445–1509":"1445–1509","1486–1534":"1486–1534","–Male":"Verstorben","1412–1476":"1412–1476","1534":"1534","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","England":"England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Cresswell, Northumberland, England":"Cresswell, Northumberland, England","lifeSummary":"George Cresswell of Cresswell wurde 1445 in Northumberland, England, als Sohn von John de Cresswell geboren. Er hatte mindestens 2 Söhne. Er starb 1509 im Alter von 64 Jahren in England."},"ht":{"1445–1509":"1445–1509","1486–1534":"1486–1534","–Male":"Desede","1412–1476":"1412–1476","1534":"1534","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1486":